@node "REGISTER" "How To Register"
@next "KEYFILE"
@prev "COPYRIGHTS"

  @{u}A registration is possible in two ways:@{uu}

  1) @{u}via snail mail@{uu}
  
     - You can pay by remittance or with a cheque.
     - The @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0} will be send on a disk (HD or DD).
       Please send me an Amiga-formated disk and a prepaid enveloped with your
       address. You will then get the latest version of T.U.R.D. II.
     - The @{"registration form" system "ed TURD_II.regist window con:0/11/800/300/Registration:/CLOSE"} can be placed on the disk as ASCII-file or
       added separatly as a print-out.

  2) @{u}via eMail@{uu}
  
     - You can pay by remittance or with a cheque.
     - The @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0} will be send via eMail. Obviously you
       have to enter your eMail address in the @{"registration form" system "ed TURD_II.regist window con:0/11/800/300/Registration:/CLOSE"}.
       The current T.U.R.D. II version will not be send by eMail, however you can always
       find it in Aminet or on my homepage.
     - Please send the @{"registration form" system "ed TURD_II.regist window con:0/11/800/300/Registration:/CLOSE"} as ASCII-file to my
       @{"eMail address" link "AUTOR" 0}.

  Registrations and @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0}-distribution via eMail are handled with priority,
  however I will try to handle snail mail registrations as fast as possible, too.

  See also the @{"copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0} and the @{"registration form" system "ed TURD_II.regist window con:0/11/800/300/Registration:/CLOSE"}!
@endnode

@node "KEYFILE" "Keyfile Function"
@next "AUTOR"
@prev "REGISTER"

  @{b}As a registered user you will get a keyfile that contains your name
  and a specific personal code.@{ub}

  If this file is not found or defective you may only test the program but
  not use it regularily. A small requester will pop up from time to time
  to remember you of the missing registration.

  @{u}Be careful@{uu}: The keyfile is for your personal use only! Do not give it
  to somebody else!
           
  @{b}Place the keyfile in the programs' directory.@{ub}
  On the next start T.U.R.D. II will find the keyfile and check it.

  See also the @{"copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0}!
@endnode

